            {
               "text": "### Complexity\n\nWhen division occurs, the idea of centralizing and not sharing arises. This leads us to reflect on what we know about the beginning of the universe (<htcite0>).\n\nAs we have seen, at the beginning the universe probably contained only energy, according to the models we have today. In other words, everything was concentrated — which made that state simple for the universe, but at the same time, empty.\n\nIf in our lives we had absolutely everything, just as the universe once did, we might also end up having nothing around us.\n\nThe complexity of the universe — and of our own lives — begins to emerge at the moment energy transforms into matter. This process leads, among other consequences, to our very existence.",
